            <title>[HBASE-8596] [docs] Add docs about Region server &quot;draining&quot; mode</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/HBASE-8596</link>
                <project id="12310753" key="HBASE">HBase</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/HBASE-4298&quot; title=&quot;Support to drain RS nodes through ZK&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;HBASE-4298&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;HBASE-4298&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; introduced &quot;draining&quot; mode for region servers to optimize rolling restarts to allow for multiple RS&apos;s going down simultaneously.  There is a good blog post from the original author.  &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I&apos;ve added highlights from and and a link to it in the Node Decommissioning section of the ref guide.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
